                <td colspan="3"><font color="#0000FF">A 1 Year
                ARM with 20% down payment, $60,000 mortgage with
                1.00% point would have an APR of 7.962% based
                upon an initital rate of 5.250%, 7.250% for year
                two (because the rate increase is limited by the
                2.00% rate cap), and 8.250% for the remainder of
                the loan term. The monthly P &amp; I payment
                during the first year would be $331.32, $407.48
                during the second year, and $447.15 during the
                third and subsequent years. The APR is subject to
                increase.</font></td>
            </tr>
